Executive Profile
François   Tardan  Chief Executive Officer and Founding Partner, Leitmotiv Private Equity LimitedAgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 2 Board Members in 2 different organizations across 5 different industries.See Board Relationships64--
Background

		Mr. François Tardan serves as Chief Executive Officer and Founding Partner at Leitmotiv Private Equity Limited. Mr. Tardan serves as Treasurer of BVQI North America Inc., International Services Inc. (USA), TTNeptunus Services Ltd (UK), TTNeptunus Services Ltd (Bermuda) and Bureau Veritas Consumer Products Services (USA) Inc. Officer of ATL Group Holdings Ltd (UK), ATL Consulting Group Ltd (UK), ATL Consulting Ltd (UK) and Accoustic Technology Ltd (UK). He served as Executive ... Vice President Finance Legal and Information Systems and Member of Management Board at Bureau Veritas Certification North America, Inc. Mr. Tardan served as Chief Executive Officer of Le Contrôle Technique SARL Sedhyca. Mr. Tardan served as Chief Financial Officer of Bureau Veritas SA from 1998 to November 2, 2011 and also served as its Member of the Management Board from June 19, 2002 to June 3, 2010, Executive Vice President, Executive Vice Chairman of Finance, Legal Affairs and Group IT Systems, Vice-President legal and Vice-President Finance. He started his career at the Ministry of Housing and Urban Development in Paris in 1980 where he worked until 1984. He then served as an investment banker in New York until and served as Vice-President of Corporate Development at Chantiers Modernes from 1989 to 1994. He served as President and Chief Executive Officer of Fondasol from 1995 to 1998. He began his career in 1980 as Civil Administrator at the French Ministry of Equipment and Organization of the Territory (Equipement de l’Aménagement du Territoire) in the French Economic and International Affairs Department (DAEI). He serves as the Chairman of the Board of Directors of Soprefira SA (Luxemburg). He serves as a Supervisory Board of Laboratoire Central des Industries Electriques SA and Permanent Representative of Le Contrôle Technique SARL. He serves as on the board of following companies : Bivac International SA, Bureau Veritas SA, BVQI Holding SA, Sedhyca SARL, Tecnitas SA, Bureau Veritas Consulting (Shanghai) CO, Bureau Veritas Consulting (India) Pvt Bureau Veritas Italia Srl, Bureau Veritas Japan Co Ltd., Bureau Veritas Malaysia Sbn Bhd, Bureau Veritas del Peru SA, Bureau Veritas Romania Control International Ltd., Bureau Veritas Thailand Ltd., Bureau Veritas Vietnam Ltd., Bureau Veritas North America Inc., Bureau Veritas Holding Inc. (USA), BVQI Italia Srl, Istituto Certificazione Qualita Inspection Srl (Italy) and Plant Safety Ltd (UK). Mr. Tardan has been a Director of Bureau Veritas Inspection Limited since June 19, 2003. He has been an Independent Director of NV5 Global, Inc. since January 28, 2015. He serves as a Director of Plant Safety Ltd., ATL Group Holdings Ltd., ATL Consulting Ltd., ATL Consulting Group Ltd., Acoustic Technology Ltd. and TT Neptunus Services Ltd. He served as a Director of NETS (Plant Safety) Ltd. and Nuclear Structures (Protection) Ltd. He served as Non Executive Director of DTZ Holdings PLC (now, Cushman & Wakefield, Inc.) since January 20, 2009. Mr. Tardan holds an M.B.A. from Hautes Études Commerciales and graduated from École Nationale d'Administration, Institut D'etudes Politiques And Ecole Nationale D'administration and Institut d'Etudes Politiques de Paris.Read Full Background




